  "description": "In tactical trauma care, care is commonly delivered in segments by different people at different times. Documentation is how those segments become one coherent treatment course rather than a series of disconnected actions.\n¶Why documentation matters Continuity - prevents duplicated actions and missed reassessments. Safety - helps the next team understand what has already been tried. Learning - enables after-action review and protocol improvement. ¶Handoff structure (example: MIST) Many teams use a short structured handoff format such as MIST:\n",
